Daily Show host and comedian Trevor Noah has, for his birthday, blessed himself with an apartment in midtown Manhattan, New York, worth a whopping R130 million. According to The Wall Street Journal, the three-bedroom duplex at Stella Tower was listed for $11.495 million, and the Empire State Building is visible from the master bath. The deal was reportedly closed on Monday. The comedian celebrated his birthday just last week in California, with Anele Mdoda, Sizwe Dhlomo and Khaya Dlanga. Watch the following video and get an idea of what Noah&#8217;s apartment looks like: Also read: Trevor Noah to throw a joint birthday party with Rihanna?